exam.description: Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering (GATE) is a national examination conducted jointly by Indian Institute of Science (IISc) Bangalore and seven Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) at Bombay, Delhi, Guwahati, Kanpur, Kharagpur, Madras and Roorkee on behalf of National Coordination Board (NCB)-GATE, Department of Higher Education, Ministry of Education (MoE), Government of India. GATE examination is a Computer Based Test (CBT).

topic_details.topicName: Time and frequency domain analysis of linear circuits
Solution of network equations using Laplace transform
Energy bands in intrinsic and extrinsic semiconductors
Minimization of functions using Boolean identities
Logic gates and their static CMOS implementations
Transient and steady-state analysis of LTI systems
State variable model and solution of state equation of LTI systems
Filtering of random signals through LTI systems
Digital modulation schemes (ASK & PSK & FSK & QAM)
Differential and integral forms and their interpretation
Methods of solution using variation of parameters
